Class FUSEInodeAdapter<I extends FUSEInode,M extends FUSEInodeManager<I>,F extends FUSEFileHandle,D extends FUSEDirHandle,H extends FUSEHandleManager<F,D>>

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    FUSELowLevel

    public class FUSEInodeAdapter<I extends FUSEInode,M extends FUSEInodeManager<I>,F extends FUSEFileHandle,D extends FUSEDirHandle,H extends FUSEHandleManager<F,D>>
extends FUSELowLevelBase<F,D,H>
    FUSEInodeAdapter takes the FUSELowLevel interface and makes it more straightforward to use. To implement a file system with the inode level interfaces, implement the FUSEVolumeInterface interface, FUSEInode, FUSEFileHandle, FUSEDIRHandle and FUSEHandleManager. A FUSEInodeAdapter will wrap the FUSEVolumeInterface plugin and translate between the low level interface and the inode interface

        Returns the bytes in the extended attribute or the size of the extended attribute in a FUSEGetXAttrOutMessage if the buffer size passed is 0. If the buffer size passed is 0 and the size of the attribute is 0, do not return a FUSEGetXAttrOutMessage, instead return a zero length read buffer
